snippet.title: Introduction to SARS-CoV-2 Variant Detection
snippet.description:
Welcome to the SARS-CoV-2 variant detection activity! This is a short overview of the theory and skills you will learn.

Check out the activity! https://jhudatascience.org/GDSCN_Book_SARS_Galaxy_on_AnVIL/

AnVIL Help: https://help.anvilproject.org/

Use the slides from this video: https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1OgXNEXPKhiNQvl9B6Zd1oZqICae_vVTZvDG6DEEO1tk/edit?usp=sharing

snippet.title: What is a variant?
snippet.description:
In this video, we’ll talk about genetic variants. 

Genetic variants are small changes in the DNA somewhere inside the genome. These variants create a lot of the diversity we see in the natural world, such as different eye and skin colors or susceptibility to disease.

Knowing about genetic variants helps us understand and interpret genomic sequencing results. In other words, we can better understand the bioinformatics and data science of the genome.

Check out the activity! https://jhudatascience.org/GDSCN_Book_SARS_Galaxy_on_AnVIL/

AnVIL Help: https://help.anvilproject.org/

Use the slides from this video: https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1097pZ-m7u22TBs6vqgbqPT1TH4FwdCY4P89WLTp2wT4/edit?usp=sharing

snippet.title: The sequencing revolution
snippet.description:
In this video, we’ll talk about the sequencing revolution that has made wide-scale genetic variant detection possible. 

Knowing about this technology will help us understand and interpret genomic sequencing results. Remember that detecting variants means finding slightly different versions of an organism that are genetically different from others.

Check out the activity! https://jhudatascience.org/GDSCN_Book_SARS_Galaxy_on_AnVIL/

AnVIL Help: https://help.anvilproject.org/

Use the slides from this video: https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1oWzck0r3djLUkS8t29v0D32-fnZDa7Qcb6GrO_VfFmk/edit?usp=sharing

snippet.title: Alignments & data structure
snippet.description:
In this video, we talk about some of the technical tools that have made wide-scale genetic variant detection possible. 

These tools have broad application, from tracking the delta variant of coronavirus, to locating the genes responsible for hair or eye color. Knowing about the software and data structures helps us understand and interpret genomic sequencing results.

Check out the activity! https://jhudatascience.org/GDSCN_Book_SARS_Galaxy_on_AnVIL/

AnVIL Help: https://help.anvilproject.org/

Use the slides from this video: https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1SxbYQyzJ19AmTj2ULhkxv9VZTEZjG2xePaVLTN7z52Q/edit?usp=sharing

snippet.title: Cloud computing
snippet.description:
In this video, we talk about how cloud computing and genetic variant detection work together. 

Cloud computing is a powerful way to perform cutting-edge data science work, without having to worry about having the right equipment. After learning the basics, anyone with an internet connection can use cloud computing to look for genomic variants.

Check out the activity! https://jhudatascience.org/GDSCN_Book_SARS_Galaxy_on_AnVIL/

AnVIL Help: https://help.anvilproject.org/

Use the slides from this video: https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1xj5cfJAA1vSX7GDXbGmNJlooA0lybdW4H3Ux28yhIlg/edit?usp=sharing

snippet.title: AnVIL laboratory introduction
snippet.description:
In this introduction video, we’ll talk about the details of the bioinformatics and data science behind variant detection. This video walks you through the steps you'll take on AnVIL when doing this activity. 

Our ultimate goal is to see how our coronavirus sample is different from the original coronavirus. We are especially curious if our sample belongs to the delta variant group. We will be using the same techniques used by scientists to detect variants.

To learn more about AnVIL and this activity, check out:
- Activity home: https://jhudatascience.org/GDSCN_Book_SARS_Galaxy_on_AnVIL/
- AnVIL home: https://anvilproject.org/
- AnVIL Help: https://help.anvilproject.org/

Use the slides from this video: https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/182AOzMaiyrreinnsRX2VhH7YsVgvAp4xtIB_7Mzmk6I/edit?usp=sharing
